CREATE TABLE Surveys (survey_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,

CREATE TABLE survey_responses (
    response_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    participant_id INT,
    question_id INT,
    response_text TEXT,
    response_timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE SurveyResponses (
  response_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  participant_id INT,
  survey_id INT,
  response_text TEXT,
  response_date TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE Participants (
  participant_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  participant_name VARCHAR(50),
  participant_email VARCHAR(50),
  participant_age INT,
  participant_gender VARCHAR(10)
)

CREATE TABLE Surveys (
  survey_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  survey_name VARCHAR(50),
  survey_description TEXT,
  survey_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE SurveyQuestions (
  question_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  survey_id INT,
  question_text TEXT,
  question_type VARCHAR(20),
  question_order INT
)

CREATE TABLE QuestionResponses (
  response_id INT,
  question_id INT,
  response_value VARCHAR(100),
  FOREIGN KEY (response_id) REFERENCES SurveyResponses(response_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (question_id) REFERENCES SurveyQuestions(question_id)
)
